column2: Based on the provided text, a total of 464 Medicaid members were treated with Direct-Acting Antivirals (DAAs) for Hepatitis C between January 2014 and June 2015. This information specifically pertains to Medicaid members, which is a form of public insurance.
column3: The number of female patients among all CHC patients is 1,998.
column4: Among the 3,412 Medicaid members with chronic HCV in the study, 13.6% (464 patients) received Direct-Acting Antivirals (DAAs).
column5: The country of the publication is the United States, and the date of the publication is in 2015.
column6: The authors of the publication are Shellie L. Keast, PharmD, PhD; Bethany Holderread, PharmD; Terry Cothran, DPh; and Grant H. Skrepnek, PhD from the University of Oklahoma College of Pharmacy, Oklahoma City.
column7: The study's review period was from January 1, 2014, to June 30, 2015.
